Joseph WEST and Betty Lang, Appellants, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 7729. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Feb. 24, 1936. David G. Taylor, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellants. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., and M. G. Gallaher, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Los Angeles, Cal.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered, appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
